<item>
            <title>[LU-3594] Repair inconsistent file owner</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3594</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The MDT-object owner information is trusted over the OST-object&#8217;s. Because the chown/chgrp processing order is: client =&amp;gt; MDT =&amp;gt; OST, it is quite possible that the OST-object owner information is stale rather than the MDT-object&#8217;s. Also, the MDT-object&#8217;s owner information is visible to users and can be directly repaired by the system administrator, while the OST-object&#8217;s owner information is only used internally by quota. So the LFSCK will update the OST-object owner information according to the MDT-object&#8217;s owner.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="19834">LU-3594</key>
